The paper deals with the problem of sparse support recovery in compressive sensing, specifically with only phase information. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) or Signal Processing (cs.SP) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves optimization techniques for enforcing sparsity, which is a common theme in the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. The paper also mentions simulations, which suggests that it may involve computer vision (cs.CV) techniques. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.IT and cs.SP, followed by cs.LG, cs.MM, and cs.CV.
